(476, 159, 0, 6, 1, '2010-01-24 19:03:40', 1, 'TC', '2011', 'ART', 'Chika', 'E', 'Ota', '109 Elm Avenue', 'Hackensack', 'NJ', '07601', 'United States', '201 9379801', '201 3425411', '', 'PO BOX 206260', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '', 'Se', '907337557', 'chika.ota@yale.edu', 'chika.e.ota@gmail.com', 1, '', 'student', '', '--', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Asian', '', 'I''m a junior art major in Trumbull; Chloe Rossetti contacted me about becoming WYBC''s Artist-in-Residence.\n\nI''m interested in working with WYBC to create a strong visual identity on campus through posters, zines, merchandise, and whatever else you need: I''m comfortable working digitally as well as manually in a variety of media. WYBC has great potential to become a more integrated/recognized part of Yale''s music scene and I''m excited to help out to make the station more visually and conceptually identifiable. I''m eager to work with people who share my interest in music and would love to lead a team of artists toward realizing your vision for the station''s visual identity. I have design leadership experience working as the graphic designer for Volume, Yale''s music magazine, and more recently, redesigning Manifesta, a publication about gender and sexuality at Yale.\n\nI''d really appreciate the opportunity to put my skills as an artist and designer to use for WYBC; please don''t hesitate to get in touch if you have any questions or would like to see examples of my past work.\n\nThank you for your time and consideration.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
