(457, 147, 0, 6, 1, '2010-01-20 19:49:05', 1, 'SY', '2013', 'Film Studies', 'Rachel ', 'A', 'Kempf', '', '', '', '', '', '5709714367', '', '', 'P.O. Box 204314 ', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '', 'Se', '908950415', 'Rachel.Kempf@yale.edu', 'Rachel.kempf@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'I''ve always wanted to be a part of a radio show like the shows that I heard every morning while I was growing up, but I never knew that this opportunity was available to me here at Yale. As a Film Studies major with an interest in the arts, including music, I would bring a unique perspective to the station, and in the process, gain knowledge in a field that would otherwise not be available to me. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(455, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-20 18:56:42', 1, 'CC', '2012', 'BS Computer Science', 'Michael', 'P', 'Giuffrida', 'PO Box 201417', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '', '804-822-8080', '', '', 'PO Box 201417', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'T64-28-6803', 'VA', '908257920', 'michael.giuffrida@yale.edu', 'michael.giuffrida@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I''d like to come on as an engineer. I''ve done a lot of programming and web design, I''m a Student Tech now, and I''m working at Microsoft this summer. I''ve heard of the developments you''re making to better manage and stream your broadcast, and they sound like a fun challenge. Also, it would be cool to play some classical music over the air. Ask Brandon Jackson or Sherwin somethingsomething about me.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(456, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-20 19:20:39', 1, 'BR', '2012', 'English', 'William', 'K', 'Stone', '150 Woodlawn Avenue', 'Jersey City', 'NJ', '07305', 'United States', '609-865-0080', '201 451-7973', '201 451-7973', 'PO Box 201273', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'NJ', 'NJ', '908153948', 'william.stone@yale.edu', 'william.stone@yale.edu', 1, 'United States', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Black or African American', '', 'I want to be a member of WYBC because I want to be a part of a community that appreciates music. My chief extracurricular goal at Yale has been to find a tight community in which I will be able to discuss my passion for music and learn about new artists directly from others in a manner more personal than reading about them in a magazine. As of now, I do not want to DJ a show, but my hopes are to get more involved, and to ultimately find someone with whom I may start a show. I would like to be a member of the Music Vanguard because listening to and talking about constitute two of my biggest passions, and I want to be a part of a community that will allow me to pursue those interests.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(454, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-20 18:40:37', 1, 'DC', '2012', '', 'Christian', 'M', 'Perez', '5987 E. Panama Ln', 'Bakersfield', 'CA', '93307', '', '661-858-4675', '', '', 'PO Box 202087', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '', 'Se', '907876219', 'christian.perez@yale.edu', 'christian.perez@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hispanic or Latino', '', 'My reason for applying to WYBC concerns the current state of Yale''s music scene. Here are a few reasons why I am unsatisfied with Yale''s music scene:\n\nThere are very few student bands that are active.\n\nStudents who want to be in a band (not an ensemble like YSO or anything like that) are kind of hard to find.\n\nFor such a well-endowed school, the resources available to musicians interested in borrowing equipment or finding a space to practice or perform are surprisingly limited. Particularly sad about this.\n\nToo many classically trained musicians, not enough variety. While I respect all musicians, the point still stands.\n\nSometimes I meet musicians and all they want to play is Rob Thomas or Buffalo Springfield covers. Yeah, ok.\n\nNot ok.\n\nTired of hearing Gaga and T. Swift and Ke$ha everywhere I go. I hope I am going to all the wrong places.\n\nDifficult to reach out to a community that you feel is nonexistent.\n\nThese are just some of my concerns. I don''t want to be the guy who complains about everything wrong with Yale''s music scene and idly stands by. The best way to get involved is to get involved. I already give lessons to little kids in New Haven public schools, but it doesn''t really hit the spot. In conclusion, WYBC seems like it cares about music, so it makes sense that I should join. I need to be a part of this if things are ever going to look up around here.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(453, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-20 14:34:50', 1, 'BR', '2012', 'History', 'Edward', 'N', 'Ewell', '19535 Cumberland Way', 'Detroit', 'MI', '48203', 'United States', '313 433-4654', '313 433-4654', '313 433-4654', 'Po Box 200881', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'E 400 189 626 577', 'MI', '908144802', 'edward.ewell@yale.edu', 'edwrts08@aol.com', 1, 'United States', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'American Indian or Alaska', '', 'I have always loved to talk. Throughout my life I have participated in a number of oratorical positions (sermons at church, oratorical competitions, and debate), have usually excelled, and have always enjoyed it immensely. So this is one of my reasons for wanting to join wybc. Most importantly, I want to join wybc because it is a perfect prep for my career choice- sports broadcasting. Many of the top sports broadcasters (Merv Albert, Bob Costas, and Mike Tirico) started on the radio so I want to continue in this tradition. I keep up with a lot of sports blogs, religiously watch ESPN, and I am planning on interning at either ESPN or at a local station in my hometown of Detroit. Finally, I really hope to join the team and make ywbc even better. Thank you for the opportunity.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(452, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-20 13:25:11', 1, 'JE', '2013', 'Undecided', 'Samuel', 'E', 'Sullivan', '341 Clinton Street', 'Brooklyn', 'NY', '11231', '', '718 702 9341', '', '', 'PO Box 202738', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '', 'Se', 'ses28', 'samuel.sullivan@yale.edu', 'samuel.sullivan@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'As a prospective American studies major, I get excited by the idea of participating in what I believe to be a vestige of the old weird America--relative of the medicine show, the thing that made rappers famous before the internet, home of the pledge drive--radio. On a less oddball note, I just really want to get into the Yale music scene and think this would be a great way to help out. Cheers. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(451, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-19 18:15:27', 1, 'SM', '2013', 'Undeclared', 'Katherine', 'L', 'Ruffing', '83 Orchard Rd', 'Briarcliff Manor', 'NY', '10510', 'USA', '914 462 2305', '', '', 'PO Box 204956', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '739462320', 'NY', '908864344', 'katherine.ruffing@yale.edu', 'katherine.ruffing@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I listen to music like it''s my job. When I saw your poster on cross campus I knew I had to apply. I was originally just interested in training to be a deejay, because I love music, mix cds, and discovering new artists, but, now, having looked at your application site, I''ve seen tons of other things I also want to get involved in! I would be happy to help on the business side of operations, and I am an avid sports fan, so I would be thrilled to get the opportunity to announce or cover sporting events. I love talking to people, so interviews would be a lot of fun also! Honestly, I would be happy to help wherever I''m needed. In high school I was editor-in-chief of my school''s newspaper and literary magazine, so I''m comfortable leading teams, meeting deadlines, and I''m proficient in a number of computer programs. I''m a quick learner, super easy going, and I think I''d make a great addition to your team!\nBefore I saw your sign, I knew next to nothing about WYBC, and I would love to help you guys reach out to the yale community. This seems to be an incredible outlet for student creativity; I think more people should know about it! Thanks for taking the time to consider my application, I hope to see you soon! - Katie', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(449, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-19 00:04:24', 1, 'PC', '2012', 'American Studies', 'Willi', 'R', 'Rechler', '7 Greenhouse Lane', 'Brookville', 'NY', '11545', '', '516 551 1338', '', '', 'P.O. Box 203423', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '', 'Se', '907976689', 'willi.rechler@yale.edu', 'willir328@aol.com', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'None', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I would like to train to be a member of WYBC because I am currently working on a radio show called Sex Talk on WYBCX. The two co-hosts of the radio show were able to sign up for training in the fall, but I missed the sign up and would like to be trained in the spring or in future semesters. I would like to have a better understanding of the workings of WYBC and feel that I can contribute more to WYBC, which is helping me, by becoming a member. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(450, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-19 17:15:51', 1, 'SY', '2010', 'Political Science', 'Hannah', 'M', 'Smith', '26621 Jefferson CT', 'Bay Village', 'OH', '44140', '', '4405548974', '', '', 'PO Box 203652 ', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'SS877037', 'OH', '905274862', 'hannah.smith@yale.edu', 'hannah.smith@Yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I am extremely interested ever since I can remember.  I have been involved in sports my entire life both as a member of a team as well as a dedicated fan.  Especially being from Cleveland, dedication and loyalty to sports is all I have ever known.  I am involved in the Athletic Department at Yale and have been an regular listener to the sports broadcasts and would like to participate calling games as well. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(448, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-18 16:07:00', 1, 'BR', '2012', 'Economics/Political Science', 'Sohara', '', 'Mehroze', 'Apartment 303, House 13, Road 14, Sector 9, Uttara', 'Dhaka', '', 'N/A', 'Bangladesh', '203 675 2328', '', '', '201220', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'N/A', 'CT', '908133803', 'sohara.shachi@yale.edu', 'sohara.shachi@yale.edu', 0, 'Bangladesh', 'Student', '', 'None', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Asian', '', 'When I was in Bangladesh (my home country) I was a regular audience of various radio programs. I loved public speaking, music, and interacting with people and I wanted to get involved with it but the curriculum structure back home eliminated any such possibilities. The radio station jobs did not provide enough flexibility to enable full time students to work.  It was one of those things that I considered I would do some time in the future.\n\nDuring my freshmen year, unfortunately, I did not come across the WYBC. I heard about the radio station from one of my friends who recently joined and now hosts the show. If chosen to be a member this would be the perfect platform to actualize the aspirations I have had since school life. It would also equip me with the skills I would need if I choose to work in this field after graduation. Furthermore, I would have the opportunity to meet the wonderful community of Yalies involved with the WYBC.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(447, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-17 16:42:21', 1, 'TC', '2012', 'English', 'Austin', 'M', 'Bernhardt', '429 Round Hill Road', 'Roslyn Heights', 'NY', '11577', '', '(516) 209-7661', '', '', 'P.O. Box 205788', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '890847029', 'NY', '908008411', 'austin.bernhardt@yale.edu', 'austin.bernhardt@yale.edu', 1, '', 'student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I grew up in a family that listens to NPR religiously, and I have developed a faith in the power of radio to entertain, educate, and bring people together. I believe that radio has a unique ability to engage the listener and to bring people into the presence of something new. I think radio is a dynamic form capable of adapting to changing times; it is a medium grounded in the past but with an eye continuously pointed towards the future. I want to be part of that dialogue. I am interested in hosting a talk show specifically because radio is the only medium that delivers the human voice--and only the human voice--directly.\n\nRadio is in a constant battle to remain relevant in a world full of increasingly complicated media. There is something reassuring in the simplicity of radio. I want to join WYBC so that I can promote and propagate the love that I have learned to have for radio.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(446, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-16 03:37:28', 1, 'SM', '2013', 'Undeclared', 'Jacob', 'K', 'Paul', '2 Collyer Place', 'White Plains', 'NY', '10605', 'United States', '914 419 5912', '', '', '', '', 'Se', '', '978711353', 'NY', '908848364', 'jacob.paul@yale.edu', 'jacobkpaul@gmail.com', 1, 'United States', 'Student', '', 'Podcasts for New Amsterdam Records', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I am interested in working with WYBC to help produce live music shows in New Haven.  As a volunteer and distributor of Brooklyn''s SHOWPAPER, I have experience with organizing and executing DIY shows in the New York area.  I would like to put my experience and contacts to work for the Yale community in New Haven.  I am also an experienced podcaster, having made podcast interviews for New Amsterdam Records, which can be heard at www.newamsterdamrecords.com.   ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(445, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-13 17:35:20', 1, 'SM', '2013', 'Undecided', 'Evan', 'M.', 'Sniderman', '75 Gateside Place', 'Marietta', 'GA', '30067', '', '4046429440', '', '', 'P.O. Box 205013', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '053491283', 'GA', '908737337', 'evan.sniderman@yale.edu', 'evan.sniderman@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Full-time student', '', 'None', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'Even though I have only been a Yale student for one semester, I have already noticed the significant presence and important role of the WYBC in New Haven. From organizing live concerts for Yale students on Old Campus to broadcasting live radio shows and news reports for the greater community, the radio station contributes a unique aspect to the campus and the city, a liveliness and passion for exploring contemporary issues, novel music, and a wide range of interesting people. I have derived my interest in joining WYBC from this philosophy of interest and exploration, and I wish to become a member so I can help continue the tradition. \nMy first experience with WYBC was as one of the many crowd members on Old Campus during a concert put on exclusively by Yale students. The professionalism of the event astonished me, and though I intended to stay for only the first set and then leave to begin a much procrastinated and pressing essay, I stayed to watch every subsequent set and ended up carrying home a miniature WYBC beach ball. Despite having gained this highly prized trophy, it was truthfully my second experience, listening to my friend Max Hendrickson host his own talk-show, that convinced me to apply for membership with WYBC. Though he was a transfer student who had arrived on campus only last year, he had already established his own spot on air with "Second-person." \nThe fact that students can get involved in producing radio broadcasts with so much impact in such little time still astonishes me, and I hope to contribute to this great project by learning the ropes of WYBC and eventually producing my own, innovative media to share with others in the years to come.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(444, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-01-13 17:26:25', 1, 'BR', '2011', 'History', 'Ryan', 'S', 'Carter', '4234 So. St. Lawrence Ave.', 'Chicago', 'IL', '60653', '', '773-931-0932', '773-663-5298', '', 'P.O. Box 200576', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'C636-7208-9201', 'IL', '907055646', 'ryan.carter@yale.edu', 'ryan.carter@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'None', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Black or African American', '', 'There are many reasons why I would like to be a member of WYBC. Radio has been a passion of mine for many years. Growing up in Chicago, I listened to the various DJs on R&B, hip-hop and old school stations. I liked how they connected the music with the listener, as well as how they differentiated themselves from one another. I was interested in how DJs make radio come alive, because they lack the visual element that television offers. I got interested in joining WYBC because, last semester, I participated in a radio show with my friend Angela Lee. It was that experience, more than anything, that I think made me want to join WYBC. Angela had a show in which she tracked the musical history of an artist, and one week she was following the history of Beyonce, a person whose music I like very much. Our discussions of her various songs were both intense but also entertaining. If I am chosen to be a member of WYBC, I would hope to have a show with Angela in which we have a mix of talk and music.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(443, 146, 0, 6, 1, '2010-01-13 15:50:37', 1, 'MC', '2013', 'History?', 'Katharine', 'S', 'Seggerman', '864 Webster St', 'Needham', 'MA', '02492', '', '781 534 5697', '', '', 'PO Box 203258', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'S45607944', 'MA', '908736045', 'katharine.seggerman@yale.edu', 'katharine.seggerman@yale.edu', 1, '', 'student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'Alright I want to host a radio show with Kendra Dawsey because our snarkiness will bring in waves of listeners who want to hear us insult each other, while at the same time discovering new music to uplift their souls? We have pretty different tastes, mostly due to the fact that Kendra thinks she was born in the 70''s, but we overlap enough to be cohesive and certainly to respect each other''s views. Possible names: Snark Attack, Snark Week!, or: Snark2K: Year of the Snark.\n\nWe want to join your team. We want to share our many labor-of-love playlists with listeners and think of overly-contrived themes each week. We want to rock the world of Yale radio with a combination of great, eclectic music and just enough sarcasm and giggles to keep it interesting.\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(441, 163, 0, 6, 1, '2010-01-13 03:00:56', 1, 'MC', '2012', 'Literature', 'Nick', 'G. ', 'Dyen', 'P.O. Box 1954', 'Harrisonburg', 'VA', '22801', '', '(314) 799-2721', '', '', 'P.O. Box 204945', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'A63200951', 'VA', '908072433', 'nick.dyen@yale.edu', 'nickdyen@gmail.com', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'N/A', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'Ahoy!  Well, like everybuddy else int''rested in radio, I''m a big fan of "music" (jazz, indie, seductive slow jams, and most of the variously prefixed forms of rock/pop), but I''m also interested in the talk-radio and technical aspects of WYBC.  I do have some vested interests in Yale''s musical world--through music classes and my job as a recording assistant in the recording studio under Sprague--and...umm, I think it''d be a lot o'' fun to be involved with WYBC, as a more creative and extracurricular outlet for my audio interests.  In the additionally, I have two high-profile contacts at the station who can attest to my strong character, integrity, and judiciousness: Taja Cheek, the boss-lady/head-honchess at the studio, and Yasmine Hafiz, my dear, dear friend ("ba da da dum bup...").  In concluding, PLEES CHOSE ME!!!!!!1111one\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(442, 145, 0, 6, 1, '2010-01-13 03:23:30', 1, 'MC', '2013', 'Environmental Engineering', 'Kendra', 'K', 'Dawsey', '5 Sugarbush Ct', 'Mahopac', 'NY', '10541', '', '914 953 6024', '', '', 'P.O. Box 202892', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '441 167 274', 'NY', '908967279', 'kendra.dawsey@yale.edu', 'kendra.dawsey@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Black or African American', '', 'Music has been my passion for as long as I can remember, and I''ve always wanted to share my tastes. However, I have rarely been able to play one of my favorite songs without others remarking on how strange it is, and then turning it off immediately. Such is life being a precocious indie 12 year old in a household that knew nothing past smooth jazz and a town that is the reason why Nickelback sells so many albums. But here, things are different and I finally have my chance to shine.  Being a member of WYBC means that I will, with good radio skills and great music selection, draw an audience that understands and appreciates me. I will also be surrounded by those who share if not my tastes then my passion for music. And I will get to prove whoever said Kendra Dawsey will never even get the chance to be a successful radio show host wrong!', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(440, 141, 0, 6, 1, '2010-01-13 02:45:05', 1, 'PC', '2012', 'Music', 'David', 'W', 'Mogilner', '14 Priory Road, Richmond', 'Surrey', '', 'TW9 3', 'United Kingdom', '+1 908 230 8126', '+44 208 332 010', '+44 7947 277 42', 'P.O. Box 203334', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'MOGIL811019DW9EM (UK', 'Se', '908229207', 'david.mogilner@yale.edu', 'david.mogilner@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'Perhaps interning for the BBC', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I have given a lot of thought to how the public accesses classical music. Certainly many people own classical music CDs and have at least once been to a public concert hall to hear a major work being performed. However the most consistent audience to classical music can be found on the radio. Radio is the easiest possible way to hear the greats, not mention it''s free.\n\nI would like to be a member of the WYBC because I think I could help bring another genre of music to the table. As of last semester there are only a handful of shows that address classical music. I want to help Yalies understand more about something that is often inaccessible and elite. I want to share my joy of music with others. \n\nI find writing, talking and thinking about music engaging. In fact I have dedicated my time at Yale to just that. To be able to have a show where I get to play music, talk about it and have people listen; well that would be just swell. Moreover I am looking in to interning for BBC Radio 4 this Summer and would love to be able to get some experience in the industry. \n\nOverall I think I would bring a new flavour to the team. I am also extremely dedicated to getting people to listen to music. I really want to expose more people to new ways about thinking about classical music or expose people to old ways about thinking about new music. Either way, I want to get people listening.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
