(439, 140, 0, 6, 1, '2010-01-13 02:17:57', 1, 'SY', '2012', 'Political Science, Urban Studies', 'Calah', 'C', 'Singleton', '826 Oakdale Road', 'Atlanta', 'GA', '30307', '', '4042857701', '', '', 'P.O. Box 203996', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '053057063', 'GA', '907831271', 'calah.singleton@yale.edu ', 'CCSINGL@gmail.com ', 1, '', 'student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Black or African American', '', 'Okay, I''ll start with the requisite "Music has always been a passion of mine, and at college I''ve felt out of the music scene loop. I want to meet cool radio people. I love to listen to myself talk." But actually, pretty much all of that applies. Really what I am interested in doing is bringing excellent music to those with poor taste. Or not even poor taste, but a lack of imagination in music, or those who don''t know the appropriate outlets to go to. My main focus would be the racial integration of music, since (and okay, I''m generalizing, but  we all do) for the most part all my black friends listen to hip hop and all my white friends listen to rock. I listen to both. Because of this, people think I''m "less black," whatever that means. I want to make a show that features "black" and "white" music that is really all just GOOD MUSIC. I want to play white people rapping and black people doing indie rock and songs that will never ever get played because they didn''t "sell out" and just fuck with people''s minds because it''s all so good.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
