(402, 107, 0, 6, 1, '2009-11-09 20:07:33', 1, 'CC', '2012', 'Philm Studiez', 'Michael', '', 'Gabriel', '', ' ', 'CT', '', '', '614 352 6657', '', '', 'PO Box 206962', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'SY904703', 'OH', '908104563', 'paul.gabriel@yale.edu', 'paul.gabriel@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'i grew up in a small mining town in Ohio near the west virginia border. the only outlet I ever had to the outside world (besides our town''s dirty magazine store) was this shitty AM radio that me and my 12 brothers and sisters would listen to together on Sunday afternoons after church.  since i was the only child in the family to leave the town, they arent too intelligent, i blame incest, i vowed to them that one day they could listen to me on the radio.  i told them "Billy, Jasper, Bertha, Jimmy, Krystal, Jennay, Porky, Buster, Kimmie, Rashad, Yoon-Lee, and Bowser, I''m gonna make it big one day! You see those stars up ion the sky? well im gonna fucking grab one and pull it down into my fucking pocket, pending safety advances in pants that allow for heats exceeding 50,000 degrees Celsius of course, and i''m gonna give that fucking star to you little pieces of shit. I''m gonna be... a radio star. PORKY STOMP HUMPIN THA GOD DAMN BUTTER YURN AGAIN...." \n\nI''ll never forget the confused looks on their faces the day that i left. in retrospect, i doubt they understood a single word that came out of my mouth, but who cares, it just makes it less painful when i don''t give them any money once i become famous...\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
