(386, 92, 0, 6, 1, '2009-11-09 19:58:58', 1, 'CC', '2013', 'Undeclared', 'Moses', 'J', 'Balian', 'W3968 Hillcrest Drive', 'Watertown', 'WI', '53094', '', '920-220-9653', '920-699-4722', '', 'PO Box 200941', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'B450-5509-1219-01', 'WI', '908804844', 'moses.balian@yale.edu', 'moses.balian@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'None', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I have been fascinated with radio my entire life, and always have I wanted to be involved in its production. The idea thrills me of one person or a group of people speaking into a microphone and that information being broadcast into space, for anyone to listen to if they so choose. I began to pursue this passion by doing the morning announcements at my high school during my senior year. This was a fantastic experience. I was able to deliver mundane information in a (reasonably) entertaining fashion. I also acted somewhat as a DJ, in playing music over the PA during the passing period leading up to announcements. This was a unique, exciting, and liberating experience for me in that it began to give me the feeling that a real radio station would bring.\n\nI am an actor. I love being in the spotlight, having a captive audience, and educationally and entertainingly making the most out of my position there. I don''t particularly feel like I have anything to say, but I have a compelling desire to be the one to say it. Additionally, radio creates a mysterious veil between listener and broadcaster that is not present in any other medium. It requires that the broadcatser have a compelling, engaging, and enthusiastic presence on the air. These are all assets that I feel I could bring to the WYBC.\n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
