(378, 0, 0, 2, 1, '2009-10-27 15:40:15', 1, 'MC', '2012', 'History', 'Isobel', 'A', 'Rosenthal', '1148 5th Avenue', 'NY', 'NY', '10128', '', '917 6785886', '2125232303', '', '100 Tower Parkway', 'New Haven', 'CT', '', '', 'NY', '', 'adrienne.rosenthal@yale.edu', 'adrienne.rosenthal@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'WYBC seems like a great community and a fun way to contribute to the Yale community.  I have always loved to listening to the radio.  Both my parents listen to NPR religiously and I have always loved car rides because I attribute it to radio.  I think radio is a great medium because people are really able to just talk there are no cameras, no tape recorders and constant questioning that goes into paper journalism, it''s just a conversation.  I have an idea for a show called "This Yale Life," which would be a take on "This American Life."', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
