(376, 88, 0, 6, 1, '2009-10-12 20:25:47', 1, 'PC', '2012', 'Latin American Studies', 'Catherine', 'C', 'Osborn', '1104 Elm St. ', 'Austin', 'TX', '78703', '', '(512) 750-8284', '', '', 'PO Box 203356', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '23056440', 'TX', '908026499', 'catherine.osborn@yale.edu', 'catherine.osborn@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I grew up without a television and got most of my news from Austin’s public radio station, which features original and NPR programming.  Even now when I’m constantly on the computer and can check any news source, I download podcasts of NPR news and interview programs because I’m most comfortable receiving the news via spoken word. I got involved in YDN Online last year in the hopes of doing some audio news pieces, but I ended up doing video instead—I did a feature following campus political groups on Election Day and edited several interviews.  It was a great skill to learn, but I’m still interested in audio.  So here I am at WYBC looking to do radio news!  I’m excited about the possibility of a radio/newspaper collaboration that both broadcasts content like the radio I love from home and puts content on the internet to be realistic for people’s listening schedules. I’ve interned and blogged for the Online Editor of a magazine in Austin and understand that the future of all journalism is the internet, so I’m excited to see that WYBC is making this jump also. (And excited to see what your new website will look like…)\n\nLearning to work the boards is a technical process I’ve always been curious about and it sounds like an adventure. I also love everyone I know who’s involved with WYBC and have heard great things about it as a community.   \n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
