(377, 86, 0, 6, 1, '2009-10-24 14:58:21', 1, 'CC', '2013', 'Undecided', 'Max', 'M', 'Budovitch', '680 N. Lake Shore Dr. Apt 602', 'Chicago', 'IL', '60611', '', '(312)-320-8884', '', '', ' PO Box 200970', 'New Haven ', 'CT', '06520', 'B313-5539-1035', 'IL', '908838181', 'max.budovitch@yale.edu', 'max.budovitch@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I want to become a member of WYBC because radio as a medium has been a strong force in shaping my perceptions and interests.  My interest in radio is one of the first things I remember from my early childhood; I listened to Chicago Public Radio in the car on the way to kindergarten every morning.  NPR or Chicago Public Radio was always playing in the car and often even at home while my parents made dinner.  As I grew older, the comforting voices and music that typified my aural experience as a child started to take on new meanings:  My developing interests in jazz and Arabic poetry biased me towards specific DJs and programs, just as my growing fascination with the Israeli Palestinian conflict drew me to certain interviews and stories.  \n\nMy interest in history and communication through news media also drew me to radio on a more intellectual level in recent years.  I am fascinated by history and how the dissemination of information via photography, writing, and radio can hold sway over historical events and perceptions.  In pursuing this interest in the past, I have done several large drawings in charcoal of images from newspapers of the war in Iraq as a visual investigation into some of these historical forces.  \n\nThe historical significance of radio as a critical means of communication coupled with my personal connection with this medium enforces my desire to become a member of WYBC to form a closer relationship with radio and to understand it better. \n', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
