(513, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-20 17:42:02', 1, 'JE', '2011', 'History', 'Randall', 'W', 'Spock', '43 Stoneyside Drive', 'Larchmont', 'NY', '10538', '', '914-715-5559', '', '', 'PO Box 204063', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '830647146', 'NY', '907092961', 'randall.spock@yale.edu', 'randall.spock@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I''ve grown up listening to and learning from radio.  From my hometown''s oldies station, I''ve learned about the first stirrings of rebellion in a deeply repressed era; from my friend''s show on Clark University Radio, I''ve learned about the islands of quirk that dot today''s indie-cool landscape; from NPR''s "This American Life" (my favorite program of any medium), I''ve learned about the wealth of meaning that resides in the simplest of anecdotes.\n\nAfter all this listening and learning, I''ve emerged with one main conclusion: There are few things that can move more deeply than a well-placed song, story, or conversation.  I want to be a member of WYBC so that I can use these tools myself, and move however many friends and strangers I can.  ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(505, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-14 09:01:51', 1, 'MC', '2013', 'Chemical Engineer', 'David', 'B', 'McNeill', '1620 E. Silverspot Lane', 'Boise', 'ID', '83706', '', '(208)484-5794', '', '', 'PO Box 203103', 'New Haven', 'CT', '', 'ZE330089H', 'ID', '908818376', 'david.mcneill@yale.edu', 'david.mcneill@yale.edu', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'My friend Sean Golden told me he was going to apply to join WYBC and DJ a segment. Well, I thought that I could help him out to make it fun, interesting, and the best show possible by partnering up to provide him with another presence that he could talk to, a format that seemed more interesting than just one person talking to his audience. Aside from that, my experience in performing and producing these kind of shows in high school was enormously positive, and I''d like to continue that. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(506, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-14 20:18:31', 1, 'MC', '2012', 'Biology & Philosophy', 'José Gabriel', '', 'Barcia Durán', 'La Candelaria', 'Caracas', '', '01011', 'Venezuela', '2034669104', 'NA', 'NA', 'PO Box 204788', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'NA', 'Se', '908181131', 'gabriel.barcia@yale.edu', 'jgabrielbarcia@gmail.com', 0, 'Venezuela', 'Student', '', 'NA', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hispanic or Latino', '', 'I like Yasmine Hafiz, Imran Baloo and Jarus Singh. And Chloe Rossetti. And Emmy Picket, too.\n\nI like what they do in the WYBC and I want to host a show. I think I can do a good job. I''m not sure I have the time for training, but I will do whatever I can to be a part of the station.\n\nRamble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble ramble 150.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(507, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-15 00:01:39', 1, 'PC', '2011', 'Ethics, Politics, and Economics', 'Trevor', 'M', 'Wagener', '', 'Chicago', 'IL', '', '', '847 208 9800', '', '', 'PO Box 205152', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'N/A', 'IL', '907097092', 'trevor.wagener@yale.edu', 'trevor.wagener@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'None', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I have previous radio experience (I hosted a stream radio show and served as a current events correspondent for a high school radio station) and I would like to pursue my continuing interest in news and commentary on radio. I would require very little training and am quite interested.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(508, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-15 03:53:09', 1, 'TC', '2013', 'Pre-med', 'Salvador', 'Delgado', 'Fernandez', '12238 Highland Ave', 'Blue Island', 'IL', '60406', '', '708-692-8672', '', '', 'PO Box 205740', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'F65578491055', 'IL', 'sdf7', 'salvador.fernandez@yale.edu', 'soxfan77@sbcglobal.net', 1, '', 'None', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hispanic or Latino', '', 'I am looking to spread the word about Mexican music and Mexico in general. So far, most of the Mexican music I have heard since I''ve been at Yale is from my iPod, the burrito carts, or a few La Casa-related events. Growing up listening to Mexican music, it''s definitely been strange not hearing Mexican music on a semi-regular basis. I seek to change that, by introducing all kinds of Mexican and Mexican-American music. This isn''t just limited to mariachi or ranchera, what most know as Mexican music, but it also includes Mexican pop, rock, tropical, and anything else Mexican. And I would also add random tidbits about Mexico, such as current news, historical facts, and such between songs. Basically, anything Mexican is fair-game. I might even expand to other Latin-American countries if asked for, because it''s all awesome, but lacking at Yale.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(509, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-17 01:11:49', 1, 'MC', '2015', 'Undeclared', 'Sean', 'K', 'Golden', '3601 Blackhawk Drive', 'Madison', 'WI', '53705', '', '608-770-6769', '', '', '198 Elm Street', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'G435-7919-1003-00', 'WI', '908985775', 'sean.golden@yale.edu', 'seangolden0103@yahoo.com', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'N/A', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'When I am back at home, away from the academic rigor of Yale, I love to listen to my XM satellite radio as I drive.  In fact, it''s one of my favorite things to do.  My XM radio is where I first discovered indie rock, music I had never heard on FM radio but instantly fell in love with.  Since coming to Yale, I haven''t had enough time to listen to this music, but I''d like to fix that.  I hope to become a member of WYBC because it would provide me with motivation to keep up with the indie music scene as well as an outlet to share the music I love with others.  And maybe by doing so, I can help someone else discover they love it too. \n\nMy suitemate and good friend David McNeil has decided to help me out with my show.  We''re planning on writing funny sketches to perform on-air to go along with the setlist.  I''ve heard really good things about the people who work at WYBC and I think it’d be an awesome experience.  I hope you guys give us our show and I look forward to meeting you all.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(510, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-17 02:29:00', 1, 'CC', '2012', 'Theater Studies', 'Mitchel', 'E', 'Kawash', '37 Carriage Rd.', 'Charleston', 'WV', '25314', '', '(304) 561-5994', '(304) 345-3320', '', 'P.O. Box 201509', 'New Haven ', 'CT', '06520', 'F405649', 'WV', '908012729', 'mitchel.kawash@yale.edu', 'mitchel.kawash@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'Short answer: Brandon Jackson\n\nLong answer: Brandon Jackson''s legs\n\nAlso, I love sports and I love performance. I am interested in pursuing a career in broadcast journalism, and I am specifically intrigued by sports. I am a lifelong sports fan, and I like nothing more than talking about sports. I was incredibly impressed to find out that I could get near immediate microphone time. Calling games will allow me to get a ton of experience which will help me improve and see if this is a career that I would really like to pursue. I feel that I have many of the skills that make a strong sports broadcaster--I am an articulate speaker, I am passionate about sports, and I have experience performing under pressure from my participation in theater--but I have virtually no experience actually working in live radio. I think working with WYBC would give me a great opportunity to learn about the industry and improve as a broadcaster in an exciting yet nurturing environment. ', 'Guys, seriously, Mitchel is awesome.\n-Brandon, 2/17', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(511, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-18 03:47:40', 1, 'JE', '2013', 'Women''s, Gender, & Sexuality Studies', 'Raquel', 'M', 'Guarino', '27 Willow Grove Way', 'Manalapan', 'NJ', '07726', '', '7328574837', '', '', 'PO Box 202503', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'G90096427455912', 'NJ', '909065777', 'raquel.guarino@yale.edu', 'raquel.guarino@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'None', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'Hispanic or Latino', '', 'I''ve always been a fan of music: whether it''s the thumping bass of a hip hop beat fresh out of the underground or the smooth voice of an R&B legend, the sweet sounds of a song have always been enough to satisfy my needs when other parts of my life were lacking. As a performer (I love theater), I enjoy conversing, making jokes, laughing, and enjoying life as much as possible. I think it would be great to have a radio show that''s fun to listen to, and that will have the audience coming back just because their curiosity is itching for them to do so. To be honest, it disturbs me a little how nearly-extinct the hip hop scene is here at Yale; maybe I’ve been hiding under a rock, but I’ve yet to come across any campus-known hip hop or rap acts. Getting a spot at the station would mean more than just getting on the air; I could open up a lot of doors for people who may not have been exposed to true hip hop. Sure, Lil Wayne, Akon, and Pitbull have gotten me on my feet at a party before, but for me, hip hop is a lot more than some tacky metaphors on a catchy beat. And it wouldn’t just be straight rap, either. The beauty of music is that it’s something much more comprehensive; freedom of expression in music allows people to draw inspiration from all over the map, and I know I can find a wonderful balance between the music we love, the music we loved, and the music that the listener has a right to know about.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(512, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-18 16:22:04', 1, 'MC', '2013', 'Undecided', 'Travis', 'J', 'Trew', '5307 Fairview Ave.', 'Downers Grove', 'IL', '60515', 'United States', '630 4180248', '630 2711796', '', 'PO Box 203295', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'T600-8109-1216', 'IL', '909050035', 'atticus5307@aol.com', 'atticus5307@aol.com', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I basically listen to music at all times. Not when I’m in the bathroom or in class, obviously. But otherwise, it’s pretty constant. I’ve devoted countless hours that probably could have been better spent scouring music blogs looking for new stuff to listen to. I listen to music when I study, which hardly ever works. Sometimes I get so wrapped up in what I’m listening to that hours go by and when I finally come to I realize that I’ve listened to Beach House’s new album 26 times in a row yet I haven’t completed any productive work. Which isn’t to say music appreciation isn’t productive! It would just be nice to participate in an activity where listening to and obsessing over music was considered productive instead of merely diverting. Plus, I really want the opportunity to meet and hang out with cool people who can turn me on to new bands. ', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(514, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-21 17:36:57', 1, 'BR', '2012', 'Philosophy/Political Science', 'Aixsha', 'M', 'Hiciano', '4791 Broadway apt. 2K', 'NYC', 'NY', '10034', '', '9178615489', '2123044736', 'N/A', 'Branford N21', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'N/A', 'Se', '908048344', 'aixsha.hiciano@yale.edu', 'aixsha.hiciano@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', 'None.', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, '', '', 'I''ve helped out with things through friends and I think it''d be a different way of approaching music and performance in general than the other activities I have going on. I particularly like the idea of in-studio sessions and the I''ve helped out with things through friends and I think it''d be a different way of approaching music and performance in general than the other activities I have going on. I particularly like the idea of in-studio sessions and the ability to bring in local bands to the studio to get a different scene than just the Yale one. I also would really like to expand the music scene at Yale and this would be a great way to reach more people and give those who are looking for that scene the support they’re looking for. In short, I guess, I like music and want more of it.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(515, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-23 17:47:37', 1, 'BK', '2013', 'undecided', 'Brendan', 'David', 'Ross', '284 Fairway Green Dr.', 'O Fallon', 'MO', '63368', '', '636.698.4346', '636.561.5988', '--', 'PO Box 200321', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'S050229025', 'MO', '908807513', 'brendan.ross@yale.edu', 'brendan.ross@yale.edu', 1, '', 'student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'Hi radio,\n\nI would like to be a member of the WYBC because I love music, friends, and good stories. My friends Tulle, Max, Erin Vanderhoof, Chase Niesner, and Will Schlesinger all work for the radio, and they all seem to enjoy the group of people that work there. In high school, I had a 45 minute commute to school each way, and so I had plenty of time to listen to the radio. "All Things Considered", "Wait, Wait Don''t Tell Me!", "This American Life", and "The World" came through my speakers from the local NPR station every day. I have lost most interest in writing for deadline week by week for a paper, but after hearing the kind of show that Ira Glass runs, I have thought that radio would be a great medium to explore. Beyond wanting to explore broadcasting, I just love talking to people who like good music-and finding new music as well. I am pretty open in my tastes, and never pass up an opportunity to see a good concert. I don''t care whether its Otis Redding, the Talking Heads, Fleet Foxes, or LCD Soundsystem, my foot will be tapping to it. I would love to share some fun times at the radio with wonderful people, and I look forward to doing my part to making the radio an even more integral part of Yale''s culture. I am ready to learn. \n\nThanks,\n\nBrendan', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(516, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-25 00:28:09', 1, 'JE', '2013', 'WGSS', 'William', 'J', 'Schlesinger', '18000 Tara Woods Court', 'Chesterfield', 'MO', '63005', '', '314.440.0446', '', '', 'PO Box 202710', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', '09161320049', 'MO', '908860978', 'will.schlesinger@yale.edu', 'will.schlesinger@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I''m a prodigal son.  \n\n\n\n(hi, Sean).', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(517, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-25 23:23:41', 1, 'TC', '2012', 'Art', 'Farah', 'F', 'Al-Qasimi', '', '', '', '', '', '2039153899', '', '', 'PO Box 205766', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06511', '', 'Se', '908030698', 'farah.al-qasimi@yale.edu', 'f.alqasimi@gmail.com', 1, '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'First and foremost, I hear Brandon Jackson has great legs.\n\nBut seriously, I''d love to be a part of WYBC because I have a lot of energy that I''d like to put to work and music and art are my biggest passions here a Yale (and in real life also). I''ve worked with Yale Music Scene and Volume in the past; however, I still feel unfulfilled in terms of being involved with music at Yale. I have seen WYBC''s campus presence swell admirably over the past few months, and would love to contribute to all of the action. Yale needs a solid, consistent live music scene, and so far WYBC seems to have taken it the farthest.\nCurrently, I''m interested in working with Marketing, but the idea of possibly having a radio show in the future is a tempting one. ', 'Brandon Jackson does not have great legs.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(518, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-26 02:21:04', 1, 'JE', '2011', 'Music', 'Andrew', 'C', 'Maillet', '306 Ednam Drive', 'Charlottesville', 'VA', '22903', '', '434 566 8618', '434 295 7208', '', 'PO Box 203794', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'T61282084', 'VA', '', 'andrew.maillet@yale.edu', 'andrew.maillet@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I''ve experienced second-hand a lot of the wonderful energy surrounding WYBC through friends, and I think it''s about time that I experience that energy first hand.  As a singer and songwriter myself with a huge passion for music, I really want to share my interests with a broader community.  I''m the Pitch of the Yale Alley Cats and I''ve done some violin playing in orchestras here, some jazz singing on the side, and some composition for theater productions on campus.  I''ve never been able to define my musical interests but some of the artists I most admire are: Esperanza Spalding, Regina Spektor, Schubert, Dave Matthews, Erin McKeown, the Turtle Island String Quartet, Prince, Sting, Stephen Sondheim, Adam Guettal, Stew, Mozart (my hero), Stevie Wonder, and Justin Bieber (I''m just a little big joking about that last one.)   Some dreams I have: to expose the larger Yale community to some of the most VITAL and ACTIVE forms of musical expression on campus.  The a cappella music scene, the Yale Symphony and chamber music performance.  Jazz band startups and small acoustic rock groups.  There''s so much music here; and to me it''s all about opening new doors and encouraging people to get out there and get involved.  I''m toying with a concept for a show that would center around the human voice.  Every week we''d review a certain tradition or style of vocal music (anything from screaming rock to bel canto opera to jazz) and then have musicians from Yale come and talk about it (for example, a director of an a cappella group, or Yale opera student).  Singing is one of my huge passions, and I want to open people up to the idea that there is SO much that is possible when you use the human body as a musical instrument.\n\nWell I think I''ve blabbed on long enough but I think you get the picture-- I would love to be a part of the WYBC community and I look forward to everything!\n\nAndrew', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(519, 0, 0, 1, 0, '2010-02-28 18:43:44', 1, 'SY', '2013', 'Undeclared', 'Stephen', 'T', 'Marsh', '512 Meadowrun St', 'Thousand Oaks', 'CA', '91360', '', '8055519277', '8055519277', '8055519277', 'P.O. Box 206131', 'New Haven', 'CT', '06520', 'E2354302', 'Se', '908834662', 'stephen.marsh@yale.edu', 'stephen.marsh@yale.edu', 1, '', 'Student', '', '-', 0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 'White', '', 'I’m interested in joining WYBC because I enjoy and respect the service WYBC provides to the Yale community and want to be a part of bringing and introducing that community to music near to my heart and to music broadly. I’ve seen some of the operations for show broadcast by regularly accompanying a friend of mine, Machiste Quintana, into the studio when he broadcasts his show “Metal Up Your Ass”, and because of that, I’ve seen the environment where the DJs work (friendly) and the support network extended to help them get started (useful); and I am friends with and have consequently helped on occasion Catherine Chen set up the radio equipment to broadcast Yale Political Union debates, and I very much appreciate the station taking an interest in another one of my major activities and one I take very seriously. \n\nMusic is extremely significant to me and has gotten me into a position, over the last two or so years when I’ve really started to take it very seriously, where I can appreciate artistic nuance in ways I wasn’t able to before, from listening to intricate and technical work from progressive and technical metal bands like Dream Theater, Opeth, and The Dillinger Escape Plan to simple, but insightfully-composed, works from The Beatles, Jack Johnson, and Sigur Rós. Broadcasting these things to a larger audience than would normally come across them on the Yale campus is electrifying for me – I’ve constructed some of my own meaning from music, and I strongly believe that it can do that for others. It’s magic, in a way. \n\nPersonal feelings aside, I’m excited at the possibility of joining on with WYBC and becoming part of a supportive community unified around broadcast generally and music specifically. I’ve only been on the periphery looking in so far, and I like what I see, so I think it’s time I try to step inside.', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', ''),
